Darwin Núñez joked about Saudi Arabia coming in for the striker so he can make some more money to afford a better car 😂🚗 

🗣️ Darwin Núñez: “I need more money, come on Saudi!” 

In January, Saudi Arabian club Al-Hilal were reportedly interested in signing Darwin Núñez, and were prepared to offer him around £400,000 per week. 💰

Although a bid from Al-Nassr was turned down by Liverpool at the time, Núñez is now expected to leave the club this summer, with all options set to be considered in the coming months.

The Uruguayan striker is said to be open to starting a new chapter in his career. He currently earns around £140,000 per week at Liverpool.

Darwin Núñez for Liverpool:
🏟️ Games: 138
🚀 Goals: 40
🎯 Assists: 26
